ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This seminar consists largely of student-led presentations. You get out what you put in. I recommend it for researching a specific application of machine learning you're curious about after getting some basic background, i.e., STAT 365.

Yes! I've already recommended it to several of my friends who are interested in applying ML techniques to their research. The topics were broad so that anyone with an interest can appreciate the class, even if they're not directly CS students.
I recommend it! - Read my answer to Q1.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I use ML for my physics research, and this class helped me develop a deeper understanding of the field, its utility, and its limitations. I would never have gleaned this knowledge from independent study or simply continuing my research.
Led me into the world of machine learning. Brought many intuitions for lab research.
